== Pusher configuration for development

On Heroku, Pusher is configured using the environment variables PUSHER_SOCKET_URL and PUSHER_URL.

Really only the second one appears to be important.

The most straightforward way to configure it on your local dev box is to set up the same environment variables.  Create a file ~/.pusher_urls like this:

  export PUSHER_SOCKET_URL='ws://ws.pusherapp.com:80/app/YOUR_KEY'
  export PUSHER_URL='http://YOUR_KEY:YOUR_SECRET@api.pusherapp.com/apps/APP_ID'

and add to your ~/.bash_login (or whatever you use) as above

  [[ -s $HOME/.pusher_urls ]] && source $HOME/.pusher_urls

== Deployment

To recreate the heroku server named zertica_connect, do this:

heroku apps:create zertica_connect
heroku addons:add pusher:sandbox
git push heroku master
heroku run rake db:migrate


